Jeffrey for dry eyelids..Each night before bed(since your eye would be closed anyway)..
Try a DAMP warm rag over closed eyelids for a minute or two each to soften the skin. Gently wipe away dead skin,oil,makeup etc then apply your favourite moisturizer on the lids or(natural products like shea butter(for deep heavy moisturizer &good for cold weather or ,cold pressed coconut oil(absorbs thru skin better)emu oil(absorbs thru skin)or vitamin E oil, then place your sleep eye mask. Try for 3 to 5 nights everynight.

snippet.textDisplay: The best advice I can give you for your dry eyelids is make an appointment with a dermatologist. A dermatologist is specialized in skin types and ACTUALLY knows what to give you. Make-up/skincare brands can claim so much, but with a dermatologist, you know you're on the right address. I have tried many different creams from different make-up/ skincare brands but none of them has helped me as much as what I got from my dermatologist. And take it from me... I have been struggling with dry eyelids and upper lip for a year and a half, and it sucks BIG time. I actually can't even do make-up anymore as much as I want to and it makes me so sad..
